The draw for the last eight of this season’s Carabao Cup, will be conducted on Thursday, October 31. It has been confirmed that the balls, will be picked live on Zoe Ball’s Breakfast Show on BBC Radio 2 at 8.45am. Former Liverpool and Aston Villa goalkeeper, David James, will be in the studio to help Zoe Ball conduct the draw. The fourth round of the competition will be completed on Wednesday night. Fixtures for the quarter-finals will take place week commencing December 16. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.